CAPE TOWN – Angry residents in Mitchell's Plain in Cape Town set alight a petrol station, ATM, a vehicle and shop during a protest over housing. A stand-off has developed between residents of the coloured community and residents of the adjacent Siqalo informal settlement. A resident from Siqalo explains why they've been protesting. They're now clashing with colored residents in Mitchells Plain #MitchellsPlainProtest pic.twitter.com/CiBQnkIdZr [LISTEN] Mitchells Plain resident #MitchellsPlainProtest pic.twitter.com/7ed90HC6o6 Major roads leading in and out of the area are closed and police are monitoring the situation. eNCA